WEBVTT

00:00:59.907 --> 00:01:01.093
to look at the Moon.

00:01:01.117 --> 00:01:03.424
And he transformed
our understanding of the Moon.

00:01:03.448 --> 00:01:05.081
The perception in the 17th century

00:01:05.105 --> 00:01:07.162
was the Moon was a perfect
heavenly sphere.

00:01:07.575 --> 00:01:10.559
But what Galileo saw
was a rocky, barren world,

00:01:10.583 --> 00:01:12.976
which he expressed
through his watercolor painting.

00:01:13.411 --> 00:01:16.209
Another scientist with very big ideas,

00:01:16.334 --> 00:01:18.858
the superstar of biology
is Charles Darwin.

00:01:18.882 --> 00:01:20.926
And with this famous entry
in his notebook,

00:01:20.950 --> 00:01:23.790
he begins in the top left-hand
corner with, "I think,"

00:01:23.814 --> 00:01:26.521
and then sketches out
the first tree of life,

00:01:26.545 --> 00:01:29.475
which is his perception
of how all the species,

00:01:29.499 --> 00:01:33.357
all living things on Earth are connected
through evolutionary history --